<command>
<name>bit is set</name>
<description>Check if a bit is set in a bitset.</description>
<type>Java Method</type>
<class>BitArithmetic</class>
<method>bitIsSet</method>
<argument name="bit" required="yes" datatype="integer">
</argument>
<argument name="bitset" required="yes" datatype="integer">
</argument>
<documentation>
<remarks>
<![CDATA[
 This command checks to see if the given 1-based bit in the given bitset
 is set.  A total of 32 bits are stored within a bitset, so the given bit
 must be a number between 1 and 32.
]]>
</remarks>
<retcol name="bit" type="integer">Bit number to check within bitset.</retcol>
<retcol name="bitset" type="integer">Bitset that was checked.</retcol>
<retcol name="result" type="integer">1 if the bit is set, otherwise 0.</retcol>
